  "text": "An interesting direction for future work is the extension of the current implementation toward the autonomous generation of robot movements that account for both delay compensation as well as reaching a given action goal. For this purpose, the implementation of bidirectional Hebbian connections would have to be investigated in order to connect the last layer of the proposed architecture with a symbolic layer containing action labels [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] and explore how such symbolic layer can modulate the generation of the movement patterns when diverging from the final goal.",
